《透过黑暗的玻璃》，寂静与冬日之光
Through a Glass Darkly, The Silence,and Winter Light

525
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:30,550
作为一个三部曲，然而，一些评论家仍然认为他们
as a trilogy, and yet, some critics still see them

526
00:41:30,690 --> 00:41:32,350
是关于失去信仰的三部曲。
as a trilogy about the loss of faith.

527
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:33,870
我是说，他肯定说过这是三部曲，
I mean, he definitely said they were a trilogy,

528
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,380
但后来又走了回来。
but then walked it back.

529
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:36,700
就因为他说这是三部曲
Just because he said it's a trilogy

530
00:41:36,830 --> 00:41:38,040
并不意味着它就是1。
doesn't mean it is one.

531
00:41:38,180 --> 00:41:40,320
是的,当然。
Yeah, sure.

532
00:41:49,710 --> 00:41:51,090
谢谢你的汉普斯狩猎之旅。
Thank you for the Hampus Safari.

533
00:41:51,230 --> 00:41:52,330
希望你们喜欢。
I hope you enjoyed it.

534
00:41:52,470 --> 00:41:53,890
我很喜欢。
I loved it.

535
00:41:54,020 --> 00:41:56,270
别忘了你的羊皮。
Don't forget your sheepskins.

536
00:42:09,730 --> 00:42:11,870
你查查。再见。
-See you. -Bye.

537
00:42:19,770 --> 00:42:21,740
-嘿。——(克里斯)嘿。
-Hey. -[Chris] Hey.

538
00:42:26,610 --> 00:42:27,890
非常别致。
Très chic.

539
00:42:28,020 --> 00:42:31,230
谢谢你的支持。
Thanks for the support.

540
00:42:31,370 --> 00:42:33,620
我看到那辆巴士，吓坏了。我很抱歉。
I saw the bus and freaked out. I'm sorry.

541
00:42:33,750 --> 00:42:35,380
这是好的。
That's alright.

542
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:39,070
它怎么样?
How was it?

543
00:42:39,210 --> 00:42:41,970
其实还不错。
It was pretty good, actually.

544
00:42:42,970 --> 00:42:44,700
是的。
Yeah.

545
00:42:44,830 --> 00:42:46,520
但我回来后一直觉得有点恶心。
But I've been feeling a bit yuck since I got back.

546
00:42:46,660 --> 00:42:49,730
-为什么,发生了什么事?-一定是汉堡的问题。
-Why, what happened? -Must have been the burger.

547
00:42:52,770 --> 00:42:54,710
你去哪了?
So, where were you?

548
00:42:55,740 --> 00:42:57,260
开车。
Driving around.

549
00:42:57,400 --> 00:42:58,610
哦,是的。开车吗?
Oh, yeah. driving around?

550
00:42:58,740 --> 00:43:00,680
嗯。我遇到了一个男人。
Mmm. I met a guy.

551
00:43:00,810 --> 00:43:02,200
哦，你遇到了一个男人?确定。
Oh, you met a guy? Sure.

552
00:43:02,330 --> 00:43:03,990
——学生。嗯。
-A student. -Hmm.

553
00:43:04,130 --> 00:43:05,750
-他是学生吗?来自斯德哥尔摩的电影专业学生。
-A student, was he? -A film student from Stockholm.

554
00:43:05,890 --> 00:43:08,480
哦。他帅吗，性感吗，还是?
Oh. Was he handsome, was he sexy, was he?

555
00:43:08,620 --> 00:43:10,170
-是的。-哦。
-Yeah. -Oh.

556
00:43:10,310 --> 00:43:12,620
当他谈到伯格曼的时候，他是不是很聪明?
Was he brilliant when he talked about Bergman?

557
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:15,310
虽然不像你，但他的笨拙很有魅力。
Not like you, but, um, his clumsiness had its charm.

558
00:43:15,450 --> 00:43:18,520
哦,谢谢。闭嘴。
Oh, thanks. Shut up.

559
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:31,090
(打印机转动)
[printer whirring]

560
00:43:38,780 --> 00:43:41,480
(时钟的滴答声)
[clock ticking]

561
00:43:52,940 --> 00:43:54,390
(定时停止)
[ticking stops]

562
00:44:06,950 --> 00:44:08,990
【脚步声】
[footsteps approaching]

563
00:45:23,270 --> 00:45:25,930
在找什么东西吗?
Looking for something, huh?

564
00:45:27,370 --> 00:45:29,550
-不。-哦。
-No. -Oh.

565
00:45:37,450 --> 00:45:39,420
(Chris嘎嘎叫)
[Chris quacking]

566
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:17,110
(温柔的音乐)
[gentle music]

567
00:47:02,780 --> 00:47:05,060
(遥远的聊天)
[distant chatter]

568
00:47:11,960 --> 00:47:14,170
(音乐继续)
[music continues]

569
00:47:15,620 --> 00:47:17,240
嘿。嗨。
Hey. Hi.

570
00:47:17,380 --> 00:47:18,520
我正在找房子
I'm looking for the house

571
00:47:18,660 --> 00:47:20,900
《透过黑暗的玻璃》。
from Through a Glass Darkly.

572
00:47:21,040 --> 00:47:23,150
伯格曼的电影。
Bergman's film.

573
00:47:24,980 --> 00:47:27,050
对不起，我不懂英语。
Sorry, don't understand English.

574
00:47:27,180 --> 00:47:29,840
英格玛·伯格曼吗?
Ingmar Bergman?

575
00:47:31,220 --> 00:47:33,260
那个住在岛上的电影制作人。
The filmmaker who lived on the island.

576
00:47:33,400 --> 00:47:35,190
对不起。
Sorry.

577
00:47:36,810 --> 00:47:38,370
(继续喋喋不休)
[chatter continues]

578
00:47:39,540 --> 00:47:40,580
(瑞典)
[in Swedish]

579
00:47:45,750 --> 00:47:47,200
[克里斯]哦，别这样。
[Chris] Oh, come on.

580
00:47:51,100 --> 00:47:53,420
(雷声隆隆地)
[thunder rumbles]

581
00:47:53,560 --> 00:47:55,520
(大雨)
[rain pouring]

582
00:48:01,010 --> 00:48:03,250
(雷声崩溃)
[thunder crashing]

583
00:48:26,830 --> 00:48:29,830
-(走近的脚步声)-你想一起吃午饭吗?
-[footsteps approaching] -You want to have lunch?

584
00:48:33,040 --> 00:48:34,770
呵。——(叹息)
-Yikes. -[sighs]

585
00:48:39,950 --> 00:48:43,120
我从《透过黑暗的玻璃》看房子，
I went to see the house from Through a Glass Darkly,

586
00:48:43,260 --> 00:48:44,640
但是我找不到。
but I couldn't find it.

587
00:48:44,780 --> 00:48:47,090
——不是。从来没有。-什么?
-There isn't one. Never was. -What?

588
00:48:47,230 --> 00:48:49,060
但是地图上的图片呢?
But the picture on the map?

589
00:48:49,200 --> 00:48:51,510
他们建造了立面，然后在工作室里拍摄了内部。
They built the facade, and they shot the interiors in a studio.

590
00:48:52,790 --> 00:48:54,410
伯格曼Safari,宝贝。
Bergman Safari, babes.

591
00:48:57,410 --> 00:48:59,310
(托尼)最近怎么样?你在哪里?
[Tony] How's it going? Where you at?

592
00:48:59,450 --> 00:49:01,140
(叹气)我还在写大纲，
[sighs] I'm still doing the outline,

593
00:49:01,280 --> 00:49:03,660
但我不知道我是否想写。
but I don't know if I want to write it.

594
00:49:03,800 --> 00:49:05,830
为什么不呢?
Why not?

595
00:49:05,970 --> 00:49:08,350
因为我怕这是我已经做过的事。
Because I'm afraid it's like stuff I've already done.

596
00:49:08,490 --> 00:49:11,810
不…不可能的。
No... not possible.

597
00:49:11,940 --> 00:49:12,950
我以为我们花了一辈子
I thought we spent all whole lives

598
00:49:13,080 --> 00:49:14,810
说着同样的话。
saying the same thing.

599
00:49:14,950 --> 00:49:17,670
是的，但角度不同。
We do, but from different perspectives.

600
00:49:17,810 --> 00:49:19,990
你只需要相信你自己。
You just gotta trust yourself.

601
00:49:24,820 --> 00:49:29,310
人物，对话，场景，一切都很契合，
Characters, the dialogues, the situations, it all fits,

602
00:49:29,440 --> 00:49:31,860
但有些东西在阻止我。
but something is holding me back.

603
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:33,410
有些事让我很焦虑。
Something is making me anxious.

604
00:49:33,550 --> 00:49:35,070
那就不一样了。
Oh, well, that's different.

605
00:49:35,210 --> 00:49:38,380
如果这让你感到焦虑，那就休息一下。
If it's making you anxious, take a break.

606
00:49:38,520 --> 00:49:40,870
你刚说了"写"。现在你说“不要写”。
You just said "write". Now you say "don't write".

607
00:49:41,010 --> 00:49:42,840
这没有帮助。这并不容易!
That doesn't help. It's not easy!

608
00:49:42,980 --> 00:49:44,320
你知道写作对我来说有多难。
You know how hard writing is for me.

609
00:49:44,460 --> 00:49:45,560
它是折磨。
It's--it's torture.

610
00:49:45,700 --> 00:49:47,050
这是自己造成的痛苦。
It's self-inflicted agony.

611
00:49:47,190 --> 00:49:48,600
这是石头上流出的血。
It's blood from a stone.

612
00:49:48,740 --> 00:49:53,260
好吧，那就干点别的吧!
Well, then, do something else!

613
00:49:53,400 --> 00:49:55,610
是吗，全职家庭主妇?
Yeah, like what, full-time housewife?

614
00:49:55,750 --> 00:49:57,680
这是一个光荣的职业。
Well, it's an honorable profession.

615
00:50:03,510 --> 00:50:06,760
你知道，写作对你来说没必要这么困难。
You know, there's no reason writing has to be so difficult for you.

616
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:08,720
你不是15。你已长大。
You're not 15. You've outgrown that.

617
00:50:08,860 --> 00:50:11,590
也许我是，因为我没有。
Well, maybe I am because I haven't.

618
00:50:14,900 --> 00:50:16,390
写别的东西。
Write something else.

619
00:50:16,530 --> 00:50:17,730
我又不是有一堆项目要做
It's not like I have a ton of projects

620
00:50:17,870 --> 00:50:19,530
在我的脑海里排成一行。
lined up in my head.

621
00:50:21,530 --> 00:50:23,670
我真的以为你会鼓励我。
I really thought you would encourage me.

622
00:50:23,810 --> 00:50:25,020
我尝试。
I'm trying.

623
00:50:26,600 --> 00:50:28,920
你知道我喜欢你的作品。
You know I love your work.

624
00:50:32,270 --> 00:50:34,410
你的事情怎么样了?
How's your thing going?

625
00:50:34,540 --> 00:50:36,790
事实上，还不错。
Um, pretty good, actually.

626
00:50:38,060 --> 00:50:39,450
它是什么?
What's it about?

627
00:50:39,580 --> 00:50:41,270
这是,嗯,
It's about, um,

628
00:50:41,410 --> 00:50:45,140
看不见的东西是如何循环的
how invisible things circulate

629
00:50:45,280 --> 00:50:47,180
在几。
within a couple.

630
00:50:48,760 --> 00:50:50,390
和这个故事吗?
And the story?

631
00:50:53,420 --> 00:50:55,810
你怎么什么都不告诉我?我什么都告诉你。
Why don't you ever tell me anything? I tell you everything.

632
00:50:55,940 --> 00:50:57,950
-我可不想扫你的兴。-哦。
-Don't wanna jinx it. -Oh.

633
00:51:00,360 --> 00:51:02,050
你能告诉我它发生在哪里吗?
Can you tell me where it takes place?

634
00:51:02,190 --> 00:51:03,260
在这里。
Here.

635
00:51:03,400 --> 00:51:05,330
在这儿?法吗?-是的。
-Here?! Faro? -Yeah.

636
00:51:05,470 --> 00:51:07,270
别说得好像我应该知道似的。
Don't say that like I'm supposed to know.

637
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:08,750
-嗯，我以为你说了。-不,我没有,
-Well, I thought you did. -No, I don't,

638
00:51:08,890 --> 00:51:10,750
因为你什么都不告诉我。
because you don't tell me anything.

639
00:51:17,930 --> 00:51:19,970
-[托尼]我有头衔了。-嗯。
-[Tony] I've got a title. -Mmm.

640
00:51:20,110 --> 00:51:22,730
你可以保守秘密。
You can keep it to yourself.

641
00:51:23,630 --> 00:51:25,910
(雨声)
[rain pattering]

642
00:51:48,690 --> 00:51:50,790
有什么事吗?
What's the matter?

643
00:51:57,250 --> 00:51:59,110
是你的剧本吗?
Is it your script?

644
00:52:10,330 --> 00:52:12,190
琼小姐，你想回家吗?
Miss June, you want to go home?

645
00:52:12,330 --> 00:52:14,260
你确定吗?
You sure?

646
00:52:18,160 --> 00:52:20,060
(悄悄哭泣)
[sobs quietly]

647
00:52:23,550 --> 00:52:25,650
(鸟唱歌)
[birds singing]

648
00:52:34,460 --> 00:52:36,490
(写在纸上)
[writing on paper]

649
00:53:12,360 --> 00:53:14,770
我能告诉你我在写什么吗?
Can I tell you about what I'm writing?

650
00:53:14,910 --> 00:53:16,770
是的。
Yeah.

651
00:53:18,360 --> 00:53:20,920
这是一个更长的故事的最后一集。
It's the last episode of a longer story.

652
00:53:21,050 --> 00:53:23,540
所以，也许它太脆弱了，不够拍电影，
So, maybe it's too flimsy and not enough for a movie,

653
00:53:23,680 --> 00:53:26,270
-但我想听听你的意见。-好的。
-but I would like your opinion. -Okay.

654
00:53:26,410 --> 00:53:28,920
所以它发生了
So it takes place

655
00:53:29,060 --> 00:53:32,270
在婚礼上呆了三天
over three days at a wedding.

656
00:53:33,790 --> 00:53:35,280
我还不知道在哪里
I don't know where yet,

657
00:53:35,410 --> 00:53:39,070
但也许像这样的地方。
but maybe a place like here.

658
00:53:39,210 --> 00:53:40,830
像法。
Like Faro.

659
00:53:40,970 --> 00:53:43,910
一个岛屿，实际上会很好。
An island, actually, would work very well.

660
00:53:44,040 --> 00:53:47,320
可以从飞机上开始。
Um, and it could start on the plane.

661
00:53:47,460 --> 00:53:49,700
或者在船上。
Or maybe on a boat.

662
00:53:49,840 --> 00:53:51,640
(神奇的音乐)
[magical music]

663
00:53:51,780 --> 00:53:53,600
[克里斯]我们在波罗的海的渡船上，
[Chris] So, we're on a ferry in the Baltic Sea,

664
00:53:53,740 --> 00:53:55,780
从大陆到哥特兰
from the mainland to Gotland.

665
00:53:55,920 --> 00:53:58,920
要四个小时的车程，而且现在是春天。
It's a four-hour ride, and it's spring.

666
00:53:59,060 --> 00:54:01,650
或许应该是夏天。
Or maybe it should be summer.

667
00:54:01,790 --> 00:54:03,300
这是夏末。
It's late summer.

668
00:54:03,440 --> 00:54:05,000
(聊天)
[chatter]

669
00:54:05,130 --> 00:54:06,930
一个年轻的女人望着远方。
A young woman looks into the distance.

670
00:54:07,070 --> 00:54:09,170
她的名字叫艾米。
Her name is Amy.

671
00:54:09,310 --> 00:54:12,760
她和我差不多大，或者比我小一点。
She's about my age or maybe a bit younger.

672
00:54:12,900 --> 00:54:15,630
假设她28岁。
Let's say she's 28.

673
00:54:15,760 --> 00:54:19,180
(音乐继续)
[music continues]

674
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:23,500
她是这部电影的主角。
She's the main character of the film.

675
00:54:23,630 --> 00:54:26,290
她那天早上从纽约到达了斯德哥尔摩。
She arrived in Stockholm that morning from New York.

676
00:54:26,430 --> 00:54:28,540
她是来参加老朋友妮珂莱特的婚礼的，
She's come for the wedding of an old friend, Nicolette,

677
00:54:28,670 --> 00:54:33,200
她要嫁给一个叫乔纳斯的瑞典人
who's marrying a Swede named Jonas.

678
00:54:33,330 --> 00:54:34,990
庆祝活动在一个岛上举行
The celebration takes place on an island

679
00:54:35,130 --> 00:54:37,130
在哥特兰的北端。
off the northern tip of Gotland.

680
00:54:37,270 --> 00:54:39,370
一个叫法罗的岛。
An island called Faro.

681
00:54:39,510 --> 00:54:41,890
这对艾米来说并非无关紧要
Which is hardly insignificant to Amy,

682
00:54:42,030 --> 00:54:44,310
-因为她是导演。-好的。
-as she's a director. -Alright.

683
00:54:44,450 --> 00:54:47,870
伯格曼在她的想象中占据了非常重要的位置。
And Bergman occupies a very important place in her imagination.

684
00:54:48,000 --> 00:54:50,730
对很多人来说，他是令人敬畏的推荐人，
For many, he's a formidable reference,

685
00:54:50,870 --> 00:54:53,010
但对她来说，他是……
but for her, he is...

686
00:54:53,150 --> 00:54:55,910
一种避难所，一种安慰。
sort of refuge, a consolation.

687
00:54:56,050 --> 00:54:58,360
-嗯。——然而……
-Mm-hmm. -And yet...

688
00:54:58,500 --> 00:55:01,400
但她现在想的不是他。
and yet it's not him she's thinking about right now.

689
00:55:01,530 --> 00:55:04,330
另一个男人占据了她的思想。
Another man is monopolizing her thoughts.

690
00:55:04,470 --> 00:55:06,920
他的名字叫约瑟夫。
Joseph is his name.

691
00:55:07,060 --> 00:55:09,400
约瑟夫，她不能放手。
Joseph she can't let go.

692
00:55:09,540 --> 00:55:13,930
艾米15岁的时候遇到了17岁的约瑟夫。
Amy was 15 when she met Joseph, who was 17.

693
00:55:14,060 --> 00:55:19,030
他们像青少年一样热烈而笨拙地爱着对方。
They loved each other passionately and awkwardly, like teenagers do.

694
00:55:19,170 --> 00:55:21,520
他们把对方撕成碎片。
And they tore each other to pieces.

695
00:55:21,660 --> 00:55:25,210
约瑟夫在艾米18岁那天离开了她。
Joseph left Amy the day she turned 18.

696
00:55:26,800 --> 00:55:28,350
他们各走各的路，
They each went their own ways,

697
00:55:28,490 --> 00:55:30,600
但艾米从未忘记约瑟夫。
but Amy never forgot Joseph.

698
00:55:30,740 --> 00:55:33,190
当他们多年后再次见面时，
When they saw each other again years later,

699
00:55:33,330 --> 00:55:36,050
他们意识到他们的感情还在。
they realized that their feelings were still there.

700
00:55:36,190 --> 00:55:38,710
吸引力仍然是压倒性的。
The attraction was still overwhelming.

701
00:55:40,060 --> 00:55:41,260
他们成了恋人。
They became lovers.

702
00:55:41,400 --> 00:55:43,230
他们更成熟，
They were more mature,

703
00:55:43,370 --> 00:55:45,200
更好地理解彼此，
understood each other better,

